Manipulate tibbles

Source: R/tbl_df.R
tibble-methods.Rd

Assorted functions for manipulating tibble::tibble() objects.

# S4 method for tbl_df
nrow(x)

# S4 method for tbl_df
ncol(x)

# S4 method for tbl_df
as.list(x)

Arguments

x

tibble::tibble() object.

Details

The following methods are provided from manipulating tibble::tibble() objects.

nrow

extract integer number of rows.

ncol

extract integer number of columns.

as.list

convert to a list.

print

print the object.

Examples

# load tibble package
require(tibble)
#> Loading required package: tibble

# make tibble
a <- tibble(value = seq_len(5))

# number of rows
nrow(a)
#> [1] 5

# number of columns
ncol(a)
#> [1] 1

# convert to list
as.list(a)
#> $value
#> [1] 1 2 3 4 5
#>
